# Trivy misconfiguration findings accepted for this project.
# Each entry includes an explanation of why the finding is acceptable here.

# DS002: Image should not be run as root.
# This Dockerfile intentionally starts as root so that entrypoint.sh can
# self-heal /data directory ownership at container startup — the same pattern
# used by PostgreSQL, Redis, Nginx, and many other production container images.
# Privileges are immediately dropped to UID 99 (nobody/users) via `setpriv`
# before exec-ing start.sh. Runtime hardening is applied at the Docker level
# via template.xml: --cap-drop=ALL, --security-opt no-new-privileges:true, etc.
DS002
